diagnosis.diagnostic_reasoning: Ms T presents with a significant weight gain (13.6 kg) since her twin pregnancy and a high BMI (35.8). Her history includes disordered eating as a teenager, which has evolved into obesity, exacerbated by life stressors and dietary habits. She meets the criteria for obesity classification based on her BMI and waist circumference, and displays symptoms consistent with metabolic syndrome, prompting the diagnosis of obesity.
